23:10.423 --> 23:16.350
In Galatians chapter 6 verse 9 it says, let's not allow ourselves to get fatigued in doing good.

23:17.451 --> 23:19.874
We will harvest at the right time.

23:20.595 --> 23:24.460
That is such a great verse for us because endurance can be hard.

23:25.601 --> 23:28.445
Keeping going when there's no fruit can be difficult.

23:28.905 --> 23:29.866
I have to admire Peter.

23:29.906 --> 23:32.850
I can pick on him all day long about how he wasn't fruitful.

23:33.026 --> 23:34.207
But he didn't quit.

23:35.428 --> 23:36.369
He kept trying.

23:36.409 --> 23:41.294
He kept trying to do it again and again and again, whatever reason why he still didn't quit.

23:41.595 --> 23:44.277
And on the day of Pentecost he said, well, I'm not doing this anymore.

23:44.878 --> 23:46.720
He didn't miss that opportunity, wouldn't he?

23:47.681 --> 23:48.401
But he endured.

23:50.443 --> 23:56.770
We have excuses that we call reasons to not do something.

23:57.470 --> 24:01.234
I always said like this, you can justify anything you don't want to do.

24:03.522 --> 24:04.644
You can have a good reason.

24:04.704 --> 24:06.766
And you'll believe that reason, real good.

24:06.826 --> 24:07.788
You will.

24:08.168 --> 24:09.550
You'll go, well, I was tired.

24:09.650 --> 24:10.832
Man, that's enough reason for me.

24:11.453 --> 24:12.834
I'll explain it to I was tired.

24:13.055 --> 24:14.056
And it's good enough for me.

24:14.076 --> 24:15.258
And maybe they'll understand it.

24:15.278 --> 24:17.461
No, I'm so not doing it.

24:17.481 --> 24:23.208
And we kind of talk to ourselves into this reasoning that's really just an excuse that we don't want to do something.

24:24.050 --> 24:25.331
But let me share something with you.

24:27.254 --> 24:33.362
The reasons you give yourself to not do something pale in comparison to the call of God on your life.

24:36.962 --> 24:42.810
Do you want to know if I had a list of all the reasons why I wasn't going to go to Africa?

24:44.813 --> 24:46.155
Been there long or more.

24:46.575 --> 24:50.020
And every day someone else gave me another reason to put on the list of not to go.

24:50.040 --> 24:53.104
So on the other side, God said go.

24:54.326 --> 24:55.467
And that trumps to me.

24:56.469 --> 24:59.753
When God says go, he's going to make sure that it works out.

25:05.601 --> 25:06.162
God?

25:06.338 --> 25:10.543
can equip your weaknesses and your strengths.

25:11.944 --> 25:15.408
So if you're tired, don't know how God can equip you.

25:17.090 --> 25:20.794
Don't let your excuse for your reason to tell God he can't use you.

25:25.800 --> 25:32.668
When you look at the call of God and say, he says, you know, you had that really bad struggle with depression.

25:32.688 --> 25:34.770
I need you to go talk to your neighbor next door.

25:35.042 --> 25:37.185
You go, well, I really don't know them that well.

25:37.886 --> 25:39.588
You know, they're probably busy.

25:39.608 --> 25:42.973
I got out of the things I want to do.

25:43.193 --> 25:43.814
I'm tired.

25:43.894 --> 25:44.875
I got to cook dinner.

25:45.276 --> 25:46.958
You know, I got the phone calls to make.

25:47.138 --> 25:48.760
I got, oh, I forgot to pay this bill.

25:49.121 --> 25:56.511
I got to clip my, whatever, you know, you put out there and that person could be saying, Lord, if you just send somebody.

25:57.472 --> 25:59.375
Because right now I don't think I want to live anymore.

25:59.875 --> 26:01.858
And I don't think anybody understands what this is like.

26:02.138 --> 26:04.882
I just need somebody in their brain and God puts it on your heart.

26:05.026 --> 26:06.588
That's the answer to their prayer.

26:06.809 --> 26:08.331
And you say, well, I didn't want to.

26:08.351 --> 26:14.481
That person could end up doing something stupid because we weren't obedient.

26:14.781 --> 26:17.426
And we go, well, God, you know, I just didn't want to.

26:18.347 --> 26:21.873
And you look at what happened and you go, I feel so bad.

26:22.614 --> 26:23.315
Because I could it.

26:23.355 --> 26:24.096
But I said, no.

26:25.638 --> 26:29.124
God always asks you to do something that He needs you to do.

26:29.164 --> 26:33.010
And you're the one available right then.

26:36.098 --> 26:39.102
It's always asking for your availability, not your ability.

26:40.804 --> 26:42.566
And so you can do that.

26:43.788 --> 26:48.814
Why this Holy Spirit equips for output and endurance.

26:49.836 --> 26:51.378
That's what the Holy Spirit's job is.

26:51.958 --> 26:54.922
The big major human doesn't mean you're failing.

26:55.283 --> 26:57.205
Doesn't mean you can't do something.

26:57.345 --> 27:00.189
It means you're human and you ask God for strength.

27:03.673 --> 27:04.274
Because

27:04.930 --> 27:10.616
When you look at it this way, we are equipped with the compassion of God.

27:11.718 --> 27:20.628
In Colossians 3 12, it says, clothe yourselves with tender hearted mercy, kindness, humility, gentleness and patience.

27:23.010 --> 27:27.916
Without compassion, preparation becomes performance.

27:29.978 --> 27:30.959
And it's all about you.

27:30.979 --> 27:33.362
Look what I've done for God and all this.

27:33.538 --> 27:41.469
But with compassion, it's about bringing the healing work of God through a broken vessel like yourself.

27:41.489 --> 27:50.020
We're all wounded healers of God if we'll let ourselves put those wounds out there or our gentleness.

27:50.621 --> 27:54.125
Compassion turns doors into pathways.

27:56.889 --> 28:03.538
When I was in Cincinnati as a teaching parish,

28:04.194 --> 28:06.697
I was at the Twin Towers retirement community.

28:07.298 --> 28:15.769
It's one of those vast expanses that has everything from houses and apartments to level 5 and level 4 care nursing.

28:15.789 --> 28:18.392
It had the whole deal all in one complex.

28:18.933 --> 28:21.136
And I had the weekend chaplain duty.

28:22.958 --> 28:29.426
On the weekend chaplain duty basically meant that I would go visit people who were new or help them get accustomed.

28:29.666 --> 28:35.132
I would visit with people in their rooms or about to have surgery, things like that, get to know the residents.

28:35.152 --> 28:45.784
Well, I also would do a worship service on Saturday and Sunday, and I'll play the guitar, sing, say a few words, and then I'll go and shake hands.

28:45.844 --> 28:50.429
I think I told you a story about how I did that in Mississippi.

28:51.930 --> 28:59.058
Well, this particular weekend, I asked a chaplain if I could offer communion, and he said, sure, go ahead.

28:59.490 --> 29:00.291
Not a problem.

29:01.052 --> 29:07.859
And so I brought the elements and after I played and sang, I told the people what I was going to do.

29:08.720 --> 29:12.004
And so I went around to each person and offered elements.

29:12.544 --> 29:15.187
And the people all received it.

29:15.648 --> 29:20.453
I got to one lady in the wheelchair sitting there and a nurse with me holding some of the elements.

29:20.913 --> 29:22.595
And I had a church just thank you.

29:23.917 --> 29:25.659
I haven't had this in years.

29:26.880 --> 29:28.722
And the nurse almost fell on her face.

29:29.378 --> 29:33.824
She fell out, and I'm going, what is she?

29:33.884 --> 29:34.886
Say it, Mr. Something?

29:34.966 --> 29:36.248
I don't know why she's doing that.

29:36.929 --> 29:41.716
And so a few moments later after we walked away from her, said that's the first thing she said in three years here.

29:45.060 --> 29:49.106
Do you understand God can reach through what we can?

29:50.048 --> 29:55.475
And so in the moment when she connected, she knew that God had met her.

29:56.096 --> 29:57.298
That's compassion.

29:57.634 --> 29:58.996
People would say, well, she didn't talk.

29:59.016 --> 30:01.740
If I didn't know she didn't talk, I thought she couldn't receive either.

30:02.281 --> 30:03.183
But she talked.

30:03.884 --> 30:04.665
I had no idea.

30:04.705 --> 30:09.332
There was a miracle that the compassion God showed up.

30:10.935 --> 30:13.960
So expect God to show up when you're obedient.

30:14.480 --> 30:15.081
He will.

30:20.850 --> 30:21.672
So how do we do this?

30:22.613 --> 30:25.778
I think it's kind of obvious from the things I've said, but I'll kind of

30:26.274 --> 30:54.194
recap and sum up these very practical things the first one is make sure you're in the Bible every day learning but also getting equipped with the word to train you on how to share it with others and the second thing to do is equip your heart with prayer before you go out in your name before you interact with people these are common sense things and let your home be a place of welcome and discipleship

30:54.434 --> 30:56.036
Invite people into your home.

30:56.236 --> 30:56.956
Welcome them.

31:01.421 --> 31:06.306
And then just lift your hands and your heart by going outside of your comfort zones and serving there.

31:07.347 --> 31:10.990
Well, I'm uncomfortable with that guys going, cool.

31:12.071 --> 31:13.452
Go ahead and be uncomfortable.

31:16.616 --> 31:18.097
And equip your words with grace.

31:18.117 --> 31:21.300
I want to tell you how this works.

31:21.420 --> 31:23.282
It's compassion and serving.

31:23.746 --> 31:25.528
on something that happened to me this week.

31:27.870 --> 31:33.897
As most of you know, I'm a school bus driver, not driving a school bus right now because I injured my back at work.

31:34.678 --> 31:38.442
I'm driving a suburban and I'm getting what are called transitional kids.

31:38.462 --> 31:45.549
Kids that don't have a permanent place to stay and usually out of the district I go out and get them and I bring them back into town for school.

31:46.491 --> 31:53.458
Well I got two new kids this week and I recognize the name of one of them because it was a student on my bus that had been disruptive

31:53.538 --> 31:54.699
for a long time.

31:56.482 --> 32:01.327
Well, I went and got her and her brother and started taking them to school this week.

32:02.168 --> 32:20.370
On Wednesday, they were staying at a hotel near the mall in the interstate area and I picked them up and she brings out two big muffins and says, I don't know if you had breakfast, but here's two muffins and I said, you know, it's interesting.

32:20.482 --> 32:22.945
This is the one day this week I haven't had breakfast.

32:23.005 --> 32:23.505
Thank you.

32:24.867 --> 32:32.715
So we're driving along and chewing on these muffins and all this and I thought, you know, cause she was, she was rough on the bus.

32:32.815 --> 32:32.935
Okay.

32:32.955 --> 32:37.119
I said, you know, you've never offered me muffins before.

32:37.660 --> 32:42.324
And she said, well, I wanted to thank you for giving us a ride to school.

32:42.385 --> 32:45.027
And I said, but I gave you lots of rides on the bus.

32:45.047 --> 32:46.068
You never gave me a thing.

32:46.749 --> 32:47.730
You know what she said?

32:49.250 --> 32:51.333
She said, I didn't give you muscles before because I didn't have any.

32:53.956 --> 32:54.938
I didn't have any.

32:56.440 --> 33:00.846
Now, the hotel provided them, but she had access.

33:00.866 --> 33:02.148
She didn't have to do that.

33:02.188 --> 33:10.319
You understand, she didn't have to think about me, but she had a way of saying, thank you that she could do because she had them.

33:11.460 --> 33:18.610
Listen, it doesn't matter where I came from, God gave you something and you can give what you have.

33:19.938 --> 33:21.760
You can't give what you don't have.

33:22.180 --> 33:28.327
And it's your wounds, it's your heart, it's your joy, it's your passion and compassion for people around you.

33:30.449 --> 33:32.752
That's what God says, give what you have.

33:33.432 --> 33:36.916
When she said that to me, I almost lost it.

33:36.936 --> 33:39.099
I was like, oh, that's so sweet.

33:40.700 --> 33:46.066
I didn't expect it after her attitude on the bus, but she was loving me.

33:47.618 --> 33:51.364
It's because you didn't know how before and didn't have a way to do it.

33:51.384 --> 33:55.390
We have a way with Jesus Christ to love and give.

33:58.554 --> 34:00.317
So I'm asking God to do something.

34:00.698 --> 34:06.747
I'm asking God to get you uncomfortable in serving and serve anyway.

34:07.728 --> 34:11.013
There's no reward without risk.

34:12.736 --> 34:14.178
Faith is risky.

34:14.258 --> 34:16.882
I got a shirt that says, Faith got me living risky.

34:17.314 --> 34:18.375
I agree with that.

34:19.076 --> 34:26.486
But not living in faith means your faith is a dead faith, which means this.

34:27.126 --> 34:28.648
Faith serves.

34:29.830 --> 34:32.854
If you're not in service somewhere, you have a dead faith.

34:35.958 --> 34:40.343
So faith seeks to be equipped to serve better.

34:41.785 --> 34:45.810
And faith trusts that God

34:46.594 --> 34:47.615
won't call you to failure.

34:51.540 --> 34:56.707
He loves you, he knows you, and he knows you can reach who he's calling you to reach for him.

34:59.651 --> 35:03.716
Would you pray with me?

35:03.736 --> 35:09.784
God, thank you for not only calling us, but equipping us the way you call this too.

35:11.026 --> 35:14.290
Strengthen us by our word, empower us by our spirit,

35:14.626 --> 35:16.489
and soften us with your compassion.

35:17.791 --> 35:24.261
Let every conversation, every connection, and every act of kindness reflect you.

35:25.583 --> 35:29.309
Prepare to engage our world with courage and humility.

35:29.329 --> 35:36.560
And with what we have, let everything that might be.

35:37.441 --> 35:40.466
I ask you this in the name of Jesus Christ, amen.

35:45.890 --> 35:48.983
Great book.

